The paper deals with network planning and resource usage efficiency in cellular networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of conformal mapping and complex analysis also suggests a strong connection to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the non-uniform service demand and irregular network topology, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA) sub-categories.
